  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "2002-02-28", 
    "text": "National Appeals Division Reform Act of 2001 - Amends the Department of Agriculture Reorganization Act of 1994 respecting the National Appeals Division of the Department of Agriculture to: (1) require an annual report regarding all final determinations and equitable relief requests; (2) prohibit appeal of informal hearing decisions against an agency involving claims of less than $5,000; (3) prohibit agency requests for review of a hearing officer's determination; and (4) provide, upon request, for agency assistance to appellants."
  }, 
